{"scriptures":{"scriptures":[{"chapter":12,"paragraph":81,"verse":1,"section_id":16,"block":null,"verse_id":1012001,"content":"Now <crossref let=\"m\" cid=\"c01012001.1\"/>the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> said<footnote>Or <i>had said</i></footnote> to Abram, \"Go from your country and your kindred and your father's house to the land that I will show you.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Call of Abram"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":81,"verse":2,"section_id":16,"block":null,"verse_id":1012002,"content":"<crossref let=\"n\" cid=\"c01012002.1\"/>And I will make of you a great nation, and I will bless you and make your name great, so that you will be a blessing.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Call of Abram"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":81,"verse":3,"section_id":16,"block":null,"verse_id":1012003,"content":"<crossref let=\"o\" cid=\"c01012003.1\"/>I will bless those who bless you, and him who dishonors you I will curse, and <crossref let=\"p\" cid=\"c01012003.2\"/>in you all the families of the earth shall be blessed. \"<footnote>Or <i>by you all the families of the earth shall bless themselves</i></footnote>","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Call of Abram"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":82,"verse":4,"section_id":16,"block":null,"verse_id":1012004,"content":"So Abram went, as the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> had told him, and Lot went with him. Abram was seventy-five years old when he departed from <crossref let=\"q\" cid=\"c01012004.1\"/>Haran.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Call of Abram"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":82,"verse":5,"section_id":16,"block":null,"verse_id":1012005,"content":"And Abram took Sarai his wife, and Lot his brother's son, and all their possessions that they had gathered, and the people that they had acquired in Haran, and they set out to go to the land of Canaan. When they came to the land of Canaan,","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Call of Abram"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":82,"verse":6,"section_id":16,"block":null,"verse_id":1012006,"content":"Abram <crossref let=\"r\" cid=\"c01012006.1\"/>passed through the land to the place at Shechem, to <crossref let=\"s\" cid=\"c01012006.2\"/>the oak<footnote>Or <i>terebinth</i></footnote> of <crossref let=\"t\" cid=\"c01012006.3\"/>Moreh. At that time <crossref let=\"u\" cid=\"c01012006.4\"/>the Canaanites were in the land.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Call of Abram"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":82,"verse":7,"section_id":16,"block":null,"verse_id":1012007,"content":"Then the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> appeared to Abram and said, <crossref let=\"v\" cid=\"c01012007.1\"/>\"To your offspring I will give this land. \" So he built there an altar to the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span>, who had appeared to him.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Call of Abram"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":82,"verse":8,"section_id":16,"block":null,"verse_id":1012008,"content":"From there he moved to the hill country on the east of <crossref let=\"w\" cid=\"c01012008.1\"/>Bethel and pitched his tent, with Bethel on the west and Ai on the east. And there he built an altar to the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> and called upon the name of the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span>.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Call of Abram"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":82,"verse":9,"section_id":16,"block":null,"verse_id":1012009,"content":"And Abram journeyed on, still going toward the Negeb.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Call of Abram"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":83,"verse":10,"section_id":17,"block":null,"verse_id":1012010,"content":"Now <crossref let=\"x\" cid=\"c01012010.1\"/>there was a famine in the land. So Abram went down to Egypt to sojourn there, for the famine was severe in the land.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abram and Sarai in Egypt"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":83,"verse":11,"section_id":17,"block":null,"verse_id":1012011,"content":"When he was about to enter Egypt, he said to Sarai his wife, \"I know that you are a woman beautiful in appearance,","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abram and Sarai in Egypt"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":83,"verse":12,"section_id":17,"block":null,"verse_id":1012012,"content":"and when the Egyptians see you, they will say, 'This is his wife. ' Then they <crossref let=\"y\" cid=\"c01012012.1\"/>will kill me, but they will let you live.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abram and Sarai in Egypt"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":83,"verse":13,"section_id":17,"block":null,"verse_id":1012013,"content":"Say you are my sister, that it may go well with me because of you, and that my life may be spared for your sake. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abram and Sarai in Egypt"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":83,"verse":14,"section_id":17,"block":null,"verse_id":1012014,"content":"When Abram entered Egypt, the Egyptians saw that the woman was very beautiful.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abram and Sarai in Egypt"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":83,"verse":15,"section_id":17,"block":null,"verse_id":1012015,"content":"And when the princes of Pharaoh saw her, they praised her to Pharaoh. And the woman was taken into Pharaoh's house.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abram and Sarai in Egypt"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":83,"verse":16,"section_id":17,"block":null,"verse_id":1012016,"content":"And for her sake he dealt well with Abram; and he had sheep, oxen, male donkeys, male servants, female servants, female donkeys, and camels.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abram and Sarai in Egypt"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":84,"verse":17,"section_id":17,"block":null,"verse_id":1012017,"content":"But the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> <crossref let=\"z\" cid=\"c01012017.1\"/>afflicted Pharaoh and his house with great plagues because of Sarai, Abram's wife.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abram and Sarai in Egypt"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":84,"verse":18,"section_id":17,"block":null,"verse_id":1012018,"content":"So Pharaoh called Abram and said, \"What is this you have done to me? Why did you not tell me that she was your wife?","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abram and Sarai in Egypt"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":84,"verse":19,"section_id":17,"block":null,"verse_id":1012019,"content":"Why did you say, 'She is my sister,' so that I took her for my wife? Now then, here is your wife; take her, and go. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abram and Sarai in Egypt"},{"chapter":12,"paragraph":84,"verse":20,"section_id":17,"block":null,"verse_id":1012020,"content":"And Pharaoh gave men orders concerning him, and they sent him away with his wife and all that he had. <end-chapter/>","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abram and Sarai in Egypt"}],"x_refs":{"c01012001.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Acts 7:3","start_ref_id":44007003,"verse_id":1012001,"letter_id":"m"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Heb. 11:8","start_ref_id":58011008,"verse_id":1012001,"letter_id":"m"}],"c01012012.1":[{"end_ref_id":1020018,"ref_title":"20:1-18","start_ref_id":1020001,"verse_id":1012012,"letter_id":"y"},{"end_ref_id":1026011,"ref_title":"26:6-11","start_ref_id":1026006,"verse_id":1012012,"letter_id":"y"}],"c01012002.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"17:6","start_ref_id":1017006,"verse_id":1012002,"letter_id":"n"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"18:18","start_ref_id":1018018,"verse_id":1012002,"letter_id":"n"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Gal. 3:14","start_ref_id":48003014,"verse_id":1012002,"letter_id":"n"}],"c01012003.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"27:29","start_ref_id":1027029,"verse_id":1012003,"letter_id":"o"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Num. 24:9","start_ref_id":4024009,"verse_id":1012003,"letter_id":"o"}],"c01012003.2":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"18:18","start_ref_id":1018018,"verse_id":1012003,"letter_id":"p"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"22:18","start_ref_id":1022018,"verse_id":1012003,"letter_id":"p"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"26:4","start_ref_id":1026004,"verse_id":1012003,"letter_id":"p"},{"e